sentences: Ken Filiano (born 1952) is an American jazz and orchestral bassist based in Brooklyn, New York.
Since the 1970s, Filiano has played or recorded with Anthony Braxton, Fred Ho, Nels Cline, Bill Dixon, Fay Victor, and others.
He received a Bachelor of Music in Double Bass from Syracuse University in 1978.
section: == Music career == | === Early life and education ===

sentences: Filiano did graduate work at the University of Southern California in the late 1980s before eventually receiving a Master of Music in Double Bass from Rutgers University in 1997.
section: == Music career == | === Early life and education ===

sentences: Filiano began his professional career in 1974, working across the Northeastern United States from his home base in Syracuse, New York.
In 1983, Filiano relocated to Los Angeles, California.
He formed a relationship with multi-instrumentalist Vinny Golia, with whom he toured North America and Europe throughout the 1980s.
Filiano made his jazz album debut in 1985, appearing on recordings by Golia and Arni Cheatham.
Filiano has been teaching bass since 1980, both privately and at colleges and universities.
